Paper: hep-th/9710052

Date: 1997-10-06

Title: A new method to measure the chiral condensate in lattice QCD using

Wilson fermionsAuthors: Khalil M. Bitar, Urs M. Heller, Rajamani Narayanan

Comments: 9 pages, LaTeX, no figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B418 (1998) 167-172

Parity and flavor symmetry is not broken in QCD. Using this fact, we proposea new method to measure the chiral condensate in lattice QCD using Wilsonfermions with an operator that breaks parity and flavor in addition to thechiral symmetry.